CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 16, 1955, pg. 11 reads: "Mr. and Mrs. Risher Watts Jr....pretty home wedding." Portion of accompanying article reads: "Miss Peggy Greenlee, daughter of Mr. and Mrs. J.A. Greenlee of 810 Bryn Mawr Road, became the bride of Risher Watts Jr., July 2 at 6:30 at the home of the bride parents.   The Rev. Charles Foggie officiated at the service."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of groom Risher Watts Jr. and bride Peggy Greenlee wearing light colored sleeveless dress and netted headpiece, standing in front of fireplace in home of Mr. and Mrs. J.A. Greenlee, 810 Bryn Mawr Road
